annotation.TEXT: That was a lot of Phantos! I was going to try for bonus stars there, but as soon as I saw those Phantos, I was thinking, "Hit the goal, NOW!"
Alright, now for the voting results:

I decided that tiny clip wasn't really necessary, so I took it out and replaced it with a transition effect instead, then went to make the .wmv file again. This time, WMM successfully created all 100% of this now 14:43-long video. That was a weird glitch though...

I know this probably isn't the best place to complain about my BSoDs, but it's so infuriating how this stupid computer suddenly decides to crash on me for seemingly no good reason. It's not like I've been visiting a ton of unfamiliar websites or installing weird programs on this thing lately...
Oh, man... A bridge-building segment? This better not become a recurring thing...
That was an even tighter squeeze that I didn't quite make it through...
Dang it! It's a no-Yoshi zone... That stinks...
Can't go up there, but that's probably where I'd come out if I started from midpoint.
Argh! I guess I couldn't dodge him forever... However, I didn't even need to bring the key over here, so that hit probably could've been avoided if I had known. Oh, well...
Sweet!
That could've been tricky if the statue fire was timed differently.

That's the transition effect that I replaced the sped up clip with so that WMM could save my movie file correctly. Also, it's interesting how all of the Yoshi coins in this level were in the first half.
Oh, awesome! Found a hidden feather block! However, I've gotta hustle!
Oh, great. Now there are Torpedo Teds to deal with, but I think I can use screen scrolling to help me out here.
Yes! Good!
Looks like the end of the line, so is it boss time?
I wonder how doable that would've been without a cape. Also, I see that coin trail leading down, but knowing this game, I should go to the right and hit an ON/OFF block first!
Oh, there it is, and I'll need the key to reach it. This looks like it'll be tricky...
Close call there...
Oy, that was a tight squeeze through the fire bars there.
Interesting... I guess Phanto was aiming for my head there, which allowed me to duck under him.
More torpedo launchers, but I'm going to try to rush through this part before they get a chance to flood the screen with torpedos.
And, sure enough, there is indeed an ON/OFF block over here.
L-a-a-a-g-g-g...
That extra key was probably just there for the player to get an extra life at the goal, or maybe just to be sure that the player saw those Phantos!
Ah, you spend the rest of your (now very short) life being impaled (and I'm guessing eventually crushed), unless you can Start+Select out of the level of course!
Gonna need to find an ON/OFF block at some point.
Oh, please let the goal be on the other side of that pipe!
Whoa! Did everything just taste purple for a second?
It sure is, but thanks to my flower, it's going to be a piece of cake! Mmm... cake...
To be continued...
Oh, good. I could use another power up.
And now, on to secret world 6!
Aha! I got the saw to despawn, which makes this part much easier!
Yep, there he is!
So now we're doing this whole thing underwater. Just great. Also, I still don't need any more feathers, but thanks anyway.
Now let's see... I can go up or down here, and the l-a-a-a-g-g-g gives me a little extra time to decide.
Yep, those feather blocks back there were essentially a trap, as I indeed still needed the key!
Awesome. I needed a spare power up.
Oh, boy. More tanks. Well, at least the autoscrolling means the time limit shouldn't be an issue this time.

(About 12 minutes later, when I get everything back up and running again...) So, you're doing the Blackout Basement thing again, eh? I really do like how the blackout effect is gradual, so that I'm not suddenly left in pitch darkness.
Good thing I was spinning or I might've gotten smacked by that Boomerang Bro!
Okay, I choose up.
Now Mario, don't you go pulling any layer 2 glitches, you hear me?
Okay, you know how Donkey Kong Country hides some secrets in seemingly bottomless pits?
And there's a hidden 1-up with a Yoshi coin over it. Well, that ledge sticking out above the pipe was just screaming, "Secrets up here!"
Yay! I finished a level today without the "Hurry Up!" warning occurring!
Ooh, I can use this shell to take out that guy!
Okay, can't enter that pipe...
Yep, totally as expected.
There's an extra key for some reason, and the goal!
Wow, I seriously barfed on that jump! (Maybe there was a snake in my boots?)
Almost got torched there, but not quite.
There's the green blocks that need to be "keyed", as expected.
Oh, hey. A saw despawned. Cool.
I guess I could get a feather using the key there, but I don't think I want to give up the key! (Besides, I don't need any more feathers right now anyway!)
Oh, man. I hope I don't run out of time... Why is it that the lime limit seems kind of tight in a lot of these levels lately? Am I dawdling that much?

4 votes to show what happens if I don't enter the pipe in 7-Castle (which I just did), 1 vote for YouTube to leave the option to turn off the lights available, 1 vote for Marisa/Murasa (?) (it's spelled "Mirasa" in the actual vote) to eat Bowser's last piece of pizza, and blame it on the YT staff, because she did it for the funzies, 1 vote for Mario to take a shrink ray, shrink the entire YT staff, and make Yoshi eat them all, 1 vote to be really amazed that I haven't died yet, 1 vote to go bowling with Luigi, 1 vote to be on a boat like Komachi, 0 votes for King Koopa's castle, and 13 (!) votes for secret world 5! Wow, it's unanimous! I'm going to secret world 5 next!
Oh, hey, that flower might come in handy, what with all the Hammer Bro family around here!
Wow, what's with all these levels with tight time limits lately? I wasn't wasting that much time while going through the level, was I?
Oh, I hope that leads to the goal. I would assume so...
One more key usage to go through this pipe...
And, remember this pit in the first half of the level, just after these purple buzzies? Yeah... "Start+Select" was my friend while searching every pit in the level while looking for this one!
It's... a castle?
So, what I did was go back to the 11:16 mark in that file in WMM, where there was a sped up clip (of me repeating a small portion of this level later) which was only a few seconds long.
And of course, any cannons firing to the right are still very much a threat, so I can't completely ignore the cannons.
Nuts. I could only get six hits with that combo...
There's midpoint.
I wonder if the time limit will be strict on this level as well...
This time I payed close attention to the progress bar as it was making the movie file, and when it got to 76%, it suddenly decided it was done, giving me only an 11:16-long movie!
Whoa, almost got poked from above by falling spikes there. Better pay attention for that!
I reopened WMM, and loaded up the most recent file, and all 14:48 was present, and I looked around the 11:16 mark and didn't see any problems, so I started the .wmv movie creation process again.
So that loops back to the warp star. Well, I guess we'll head back to world 7...
Looks like there are multiple paths here. Let's start with the middle path.
Alright, Yoshi. Ready for secret world 7?
I'm trying to keep Phanto from chasing me, but I'm not sure how effective this is being.
Yeah, I figured the key was going to be needed more than once.
Well, anyway, I missed a Yoshi coin somewhere, so I'm going back to look for it.
In addition, many of you wanted me complete the entire secret world before heading to King Koopa's castle, so let's see if I can finish the secret world today!
Whoa, I almost "got the point" of that jump!
Ooh, let's go for a big combo here!

Another weird thing that happened to me lately involved this very movie file. When I initially created it in Windows Movie Maker, it apparently only created 11:16 of the (then) 14:48 movie file. The last 3.5 minutes just simply weren't there.
Raise your hand if you expected a factory level here! (*Raises hand*)
WHOA!!!
Ah, so you're doing the Blackout Base-BSoD occurred here while typing this annotation, apparently due to a "BAD_POOL_HEADER", whatever that means...
Oh, wait. Was I supposed to keep up with that platform? Well, that's okay. I'm close enough to its point of origin that I can still easily board another one.
That upper path looks like a dead end to me, so I'm just going to go straight for the lower path.

Hello, and welcome back to Super SIG World 21! Now, before I get to the voting results, someone wanted me to see what happens if you don't enter this pipe at the end of the world 7 castle. So, let's see...
Oh, I don't need the key to reach the ON/OFF block from here, but Phanto is still going to be royally in the way...
Torches and toggling blue blocks... The timing on this is going to be tricky...
Oh, yeah. Due to the autoscrolling, I can avoid much of the cannonfire by staying near the right edge of the screen. I'll have to watch out for other incoming hazards, though.
Of course, I'll probably need my trusty key!
There's Phanto, just as expected.
Buzz Lightyear to the rescue! ...Maybe not. (Good thing I was given that spare power up!)
Now, before I head to secret world 7, I think it would be a good idea to get myself a partner!
LOL!
Oh, great. Now there's a red spiky fish generator active. It's probably not as annoying as a flying fish generator, but still...
And I can't go any further this way right now, so I have to backtrack a bit.
Ooh, I'm glad I didn't land on the plant and pipe at the same time in such a way that I'd get bitten even though I was spin jumping.
Alright. Now, I know I saw another path going down earlier...
Whoop, don't go rushing forward too fast! I'm going to have to carefully contemplate these blue blocks...
Obviously a Maverick Thwomp.
Looks like choice didn't really matter here. It only affected what obstacles I faced. (The upper route looked easier, though.)
Oops, forgot to check that pipe. Well, I'll check the next one!
Oh, hey there purple buzzies. How's it going?
That was a tight squeeze.
Is this going to be another level where I almost run out of time? Or will I actually really run out of time this time?
Nuts. I meant to break that last green block. Um, can I squeeze by Phanto there?
I guess I've activated the "special world cleared" flag by finishing Secret-7. Cool. Now, I guess King Koopa's castle is all that remains. What awaits us there? Find out next time!
Oh, so we're doing the whole pyramid thing again, and I bet Phanto's hanging around here somewhere...
Oh, this just screams, "Something!"
Luigifan22222's translation: "You must not part with the key!"
